definitions.definition: A heterocyclic organic compound containing two nitrogen atoms next to each others in a five-membered ring, called 1,2- diazole in IUPAC nomenclature .
A group of compounds containing that structure .

main_definition: ( organic chemistry ) A heterocyclic organic compound containing two nitrogen atoms next to each others in a five-membered ring, called 1,2- diazole in IUPAC nomenclature .
secondary_definitions: ( organic chemistry ) A group of compounds containing that structure .
